            <pb xml:id="tr-1r" n="1r" facs="#i1"/>
            <p>Nāṣir ibn Jibrīl came to Makārim ibn Isḥaq, the Jewish physician, together with his
               natural daughter (lit. ‘daughter of his loins’ – his biological daughter?) called
               Sutayt, in whose left eye there was pus. He requested the aforementioned physician
               treat her eye with a sharp knife. If God, exalted is he, grants sight, his
               remuneration will be two dirhams. If the outcome is the opposite, he will evaluate
               the fee accordingly and the physician will be free from liability for that.</p>
            <pb xml:id="tr-1v" n="1v" facs="#i2"/>
         </div>
